package learningJava;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        //Scanner is the class, sc is the reference name (stored in stack), new (creates an object in heap), Scanner() is the newly created object
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String scanned = sc.next();
        int scannedNum = sc.nextInt();

        System.out.println(scanned);

    }
}

• Scanners are just an easy way to read primitive types like int, double, etc.
• .next() gives string
• .nextInt() gives int
• .nextBoolean() gives boolean
• .nextDouble() gives double